			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">libsrpc provides two kinds of implicit setup which make code hard to
understand and are hard to support with dynamic linking:

 * Adding methods to a global list using NACL_SRPC_METHOD().
 * Implicit startup, via a default main() and via functions that are
   called before main() via crt1.o.

We need to make it possible to do explicit setup, change the tests to
use this, and eventually remove the implicit mechanisms.

See this thread:
http://groups.google.com/group/native-client-discuss/browse_frm/thread/f5dc679cc63aaf62
